com.cognos.CAM_AAA.authentication

Class MultiSelectDisplayObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cognos.CAM_AAA.authentication.SingleSelectDisplayObject
      • com.cognos.CAM_AAA.authentication.MultiSelectDisplayObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDisplayObject, IMultiSelectDisplayObject, ISingleSelectDisplayObject, ITextDisplayObject

    public class MultiSelectDisplayObject
extends SingleSelectDisplayObject
implements IMultiSelectDisplayObject
    A display object that presents a set of selectable values to the user, where one or more entries can be chosen. If the user does not choose an item, then an empty select option is added. If more than one value is selected, then a form field variable will exist for each value selected.
